  <h1>Mostly Tuesdays</h1>
  <h2>Aegis Dynamics – Internal Brand Meeting</h2>

  <p>“Big Charli,” said Jessica Martinez, “the Tactical Foundation Garments division is ready for launch.”</p>
  <p>“No,” said Big Charli.</p>
  <p>“But we’ve benchmarked against every civilian brassiere manufacturer.”</p>
  <p>“No.”</p>
  <p>“We’ve developed Adaptive Load Redistribution™.”</p>
  <p>“No.”</p>
  <p>“We’ve got a forty-seven-page document on Strategic Bust Readiness.”</p>
  <p>“No.”</p>
  <p>Jessica sighed.</p>
  <p>“Then what do you suggest?”</p>
  <p>Big Charli pressed the intercom.</p>
  <p>“Send Poppy in.”</p>
  <p>A few moments later Poppy entered carrying a notebook.</p>
  <p>“Meet your subject matter expert,” said Big Charli.</p>
  <p>Jessica frowned.</p>
  <p>“What’s her speciality?”</p>
  <p>Big Charli looked surprised.</p>
  <p>“Pre-Gravitational Erosion.”</p>
  <p>“...I’m sorry?”</p>
  <p>“The cumulative effects of gravity on unsupported soft tissue over several decades.”</p>
  <p>Poppy nodded.</p>
  <p>“Mostly Tuesdays.”</p>
  <p>“I’ve prepared some recommendations.”</p>
  <p>She opened the folder.</p>
  <p>TACTICAL FOUNDATION GARMENTS</p>
  <p>Predictive Bounce Mitigation.</p>
  <p>Adaptive Load Redistribution.</p>
  <p>Dynamic Strap Geometry.</p>
  <p>Structural Integrity Field Integration.</p>
  <p>Jessica smiled.</p>
  <p>“Excellent.”</p>
  <p>Poppy looked confused.</p>
  <p>“Oh no. Those are all terrible.”</p>
  <p>She turned the page.</p>
  <p>“What women actually want.”</p>
  <p>Comfortable.</p>
  <p>Doesn’t dig in.</p>
  <p>Doesn’t ride up.</p>
  <p>Doesn’t cost the GDP of a small moon.</p>
  <p>Nice colours.</p>
  <p>Big Charli smiled.</p>
  <p>“There it is.”</p>
  <p>Jessica looked horrified.</p>
  <p>“But... where’s the military terminology?”</p>
  <p>Poppy blinked.</p>
  <p>“It’s a bra.”</p>
  <p>Silence.</p>
</Base>
